Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 23.04.2025

Thank you for choosing to use our services. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring compliance with relevant privacy laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), the California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA), and the California Online Privacy Protection Act (CalOPPA).

Information Collection

We collect various types of information from users of our mobile application, including:

Personal Information: Names, email addresses, payment details for in-app purchases (handled by Apple Store and Google Play).

Children’s Information: We may collect personal information from children under the age of 13. We ensure compliance with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).

Device Information: Device ID, operating system, and IP addresses.

Usage Data: Information about how you interact with our services, collected via Firebase Analytics.

Use of Information

We use collected information to:

Provide and improve our services.

Process transactions and in-app payments.

Personalize user experiences.

Monitor service usage and analyze user interactions via Firebase Analytics.

Deliver targeted advertising using AdMob by Google.

Comply with legal obligations.

Sharing of Information

We do not sell personal information. However, we may share your information with third parties in the following circumstances:

Payment processors (Apple Store and Google Play) to process transactions.
..
Google Firebase for analytics and app performance monitoring.

AdMob for advertising purposes.

Compliance with legal requirements or government requests.

Advertising

We display ads through AdMob by Google, which may collect user data to deliver personalized advertisements. Please review Google's Privacy Policy for more information.

Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect personal data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

Your Rights Under GDPR, CCPA, and CPRA

You have rights regarding your personal data, including:

Accessing your data.

Requesting correction or deletion of your data.

Objecting to or restricting the processing of your data.

Requesting portability of your data.

Opting out of the sale or sharing of your personal data.

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the details provided below.

Children’s Privacy

We knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years old with parental consent in compliance with COPPA. Parents or guardians can review, modify, or request deletion of their child's personal information by contacting us directly.

CalOPPA Compliance

Our policy complies with the California Online Privacy Protection Act, requiring us to post a conspicuous Privacy Policy and adhere to its provisions.

Children’s Privacy

We knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years old only with explicit parental consent, complying fully with COPPA. Parents or guardians can review, modify, or request deletion of their child's personal information by contacting us directly.
Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this policy periodically. We will notify users about significant changes by updating the effective date and, if necessary, via notifications within the app.

